16+512GB STORAGE UNLOCKED PHONE: Ulefone Note 16 Pro adopts a octa-core processor which strikes a balance between performance and power consumption, runs most applications smoothly. Comes with a 8GB standard RAM, a max. 8GB virtual memory expansion(4/8GB for optional), 512GB internal storage and an additional 256GB via TF Card can be inserted to provide plenty of room for images, videos, files, games etc..

ANDROID 13 UNLOCKED CELL PHONES: Ulefone Note 16 Pro runs the newest Android 13 system, which further improve your personal and privacy focused. The pure version has no ads or unwanted pre-installed software.

50MP MAIN CAMERA SMARTPHONES: Packed with a 50MP rear camera and a 2MP macro camera, features AI scene detection and HDR, delivers awesome details and rich, vivid colors in every shot. The 8MP Selfie camera is built-in portrait enhancements shows your best side in every selfie or video call.

6.52” DISPLAY UNLOCKED SMARTPHONE: The large 6.52" HD+ IPS LCD of Ulefone Note 16 Pro delivers vivid details, with a 90% screen-to-body ratio, you can have a fully immersive experience when video chatting or watching shows.
4400MAH BATTERY 4G CELL PHONE: The built-in 4400mAh battery supports up to 277 hours standby time, 24 hours talk time, and 13 hours TikTok nonstop. Also support OTG to reverse to other devices.

ULTRA THIN & LIGHT UNLOCKED CELLPHONES: Ulefone Note 16 Pro is redesigned its colors, adopts saturated color for everyone: a classic and mysterious Meteorite Black , a tranquil and appealing Serenity Blue and a gorgeous Midnight Violet. Its thickness is slimmed-down to 3.4 inches(8.7mm), the weight is also down to a feather-light 0.41lbs(164g).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent phone at a much more affordable price
reviews.reviewText: I like both the price and the quality of the phone. 512GB is what I have been looking for a long time and the price is very attractive. It comes with a case but it might be difficult to find one with better protection.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Avoid - Struggles with everything
reviews.reviewText: I'm coming from a pixel 3xl, so a big brand but a nearly 6 year old phone at this point. Even with its issues, that phone worked smoother (up until it died lol).The video playback on this phone seems to freeze/crash at least every 2 minutes, usually closer to 30 seconds. Audio is laughably bad. Even using wireless headphones, the audio quality is mediocre.Photo quality is mediocre, and the proprietary camera app needs access to your contacts to work for some corrupt reason. Power button and finger print reader combo is in the perfect spot to hit all the time. About the only good thing I can say about this phone is that it technically works, and the purple color is pretty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for the Price
reviews.reviewText: This is a great phone for the price. The RAM is 8gb with up to 8gb virtual (works fine). It has a huge amount of storage (who uses 1/2 TB of storage on their phone?!?). Came with Android 13. The wi-fi radio seems weak and somewhat intermittent. The 50MP camera, when selected as an option, does not zoom (just greater pixels in a shot?). Normal camera mode lets you zoom. Comes with the clear case.
